Please install R-Studio to run the R code.
===================================================================================
To install R-studio see http://www.r-bloggers.com/download-and-install-r-in-ubuntu/
===================================================================================
Open the code in R Studio -> To run it click on source

If any problem in running the code see 

http://www.rexamples.com/8/How%20to%20run%20the%20code

Example

1. Input - (Inverted_Pyramid.r)
Please enter the number of the level you want in pyramind: 3
Output
*  *  *  *  *  [1] ""
  *  *  *  [1] ""
    *  [1] ""

2. Input - (Int_To_Binary.r)
Please enter a +ve number to convert it into binary: 4
Output
[1] 0 1 0 0


3. Input - Modulo.r
Please enter x values 3
Please enter y values 2
Please enter z values 5
Output
[1] 4
